This project implements a modern many-body diagrammatic approach known as the Dual-GW method, written in C++. 
It is designed to simulate the non-equilibrium dynamics of strongly correlated quantum systems on the L-shaped Keldysh contour.


For a given set of input parameters, the code computes key physical quantities, including the single-particle Green’s function, 
many-body self-energy, and spin and charge susceptibilities. 

To run these simulations, we need the NESSi library, an open-source platform available at https://nessi.tuxfamily.org/

